Avner, Delek Drilling, Ness, Teva: Israeli Equity Preview

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-07-24T06:35:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-24/avner-delek-drilling-ness-teva-israeli-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in Israeli markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after
the company names and prices are from the last close unless
otherwise stated.  The TA-25 Index gained 0.3 percent to 1,263.47 in  Tel Aviv .  Avner Oil Exploration-LP (AVNRL IT): The oil and gas
explorer filed a shelf registration in Tel Aviv covering as many
as 3 billion partnership units and options that may be offered
for sale to the public or through a rights offering to existing
shareholders. Avner rose 2.5 percent to 2.148 shekels.  Delek Drilling-LP (DEDRL IT): The energy explorer filed a
shelf registration covering partnership units and options. Delek
Drilling gained 2.7 percent to 12.06 shekels.  Delek Group Ltd. (DLEKG)  : The holding company accepted
institutional commitments to buy 160,000 units of series Tet Vav
bonds for 166.5 million shekels ($49 million) and 221,284 units
of series Yud Het bonds for 240.7 million shekels. Delek
advanced 1.3 percent to 772 shekels.  Ness Technologies Inc. (NSTC)  : The computer-services
provider set Aug. 30 as the date to hold a shareholder meeting
to vote on its merger. Ness fell 0.5 percent to 26.16 shekels.  Perrigo Co. (PRGO)  : The maker of over-the-counter drugs
received approval from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration to
market coated cinnamon-nicotine gum. Perrigo retreated 0.7
percent to 318.80 shekels.  Teva Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd. (TEVA)  : The world’s
largest maker of generic drugs settled a patent litigation
related to its generic versions of Novartis AG’s Lotrel blood-
pressure drug. Teva fell 1.2 percent to 162.40 shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Wrobel in Tel Aviv at 
 swrobel4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
